Development of flexion pyramidal signs in preterm infants.

LesnÃ½ I, ProskovÃ¡ M, Mydlil V.

Forty-two babies (20 boys, 22 girls) with birthweights from 800g to 2000g and 
gestational ages between 25 and 40 weeks were followed-up for several weeks with 
developmental tests and a conventional neurological examination. Here, only the 
